In haryana mandis are the structure made by govt. This is a system to help poor farmers as well rich farmers.in mandis ardti (middle man) work for 2 percent of his commissions in exchange he provide us services that need to be done before selling cleaning, packing, payment from purchaser and place to store our crops before selling. Second thing families which are rely only on farmering need financial need for upto 4 to 6 months( crop cycle). If any financial crisis and any unplanned thing happen to them they easily Can take their help as they are their clients in exchange of verbel security of next crop. So exploitation of farmers are happening in states with weak mandi system and bad govt purchase. Prices of every product depends on demand and supply. As u seen several time prices of vegetables and grans. Govt need to assure minimum support price in writing and maximum selling price also which will be a strong step to stop corporate monopoly as they have sell products made of farming in balances price
